  "texts": [
    "Identifying different simulation tools helps network developers to test load-balancing algorithms to improve QoS.",
    "A simulator is a framework that provides a virtual environment to test performance, deployment models, resource allocation, and load balancing.",
    "Simulators play a major role in testing and validating, before deploying on real hardware.",
    "Every simulator has some unique features and is used to evaluate different parameter performance.",
    "Table 16 shows the various load-balancing algorithms/ frameworks, their simulation tools and testbeds, the type of controller and data set, the load-balancing layer, the number of architectural layers, and QoS space dimensions."
